    "description": "The so-called Church of San Primitivo in Monte Compatri. The church's bell tower was converted to a defensive tower around 1200.",
    "details": "<p>The Christian church dedicated to a local saint, Primitivus, said to have been beheaded at Gabii. The church was the center of the Late Roman Christian community.</p>",
